"""
singapore_api.py — shared data.gov.sg client for all Singapore skills.

This is the canonical copy that lives at the repo root. Per-skill copies at
<skill>/scripts/singapore_api.py are kept byte-identical to this file by
scripts/sync_singapore_api.py (which prepends a SYNCED FROM header). To change
the shared client, edit THIS file, then run:

    python3 scripts/sync_singapore_api.py
    python3 -m unittest discover -s tests

Stdlib only: urllib, gzip, json, os, time, hashlib, pathlib, datetime.

Auth: set DATA_GOV_SG_API_KEY in your environment. The key unlocks the v2
endpoint family (api-open.data.gov.sg/v2/...) which returns flatter payloads
and includes MRT train arrival data not published on v1. v1 endpoints still
work without a key as a fallback. Register at https://data.gov.sg/ to get a
key. The env var is read at call time, not import time, so tests can flip it
freely.

Cache: ~/.hermes/cache/<namespace>/<sha1(key)>.json. The OneMap geocoder is
NOT cached (it's fast and the response is query-specific).

v1 vs v2 routing: most fetchers try v2 first (when a key is set), fall back to
v1 on 401/404/5xx. v2 is the primary path; v1 is the public safety net.
"""
